// in Bridge pattern, we separate the abstraction (interface) from its implementation (concrete classes) so that both can vary independently.
// This allows us to change the implementation without affecting the clients that use the abstraction. The key components of the Bridge pattern are:


// Here both feature and implementation can change at runtime and provide flexibilty to the system.

